5:
And I won't allow you to stomp on
her work like that!
10: Oh, it's you. No, I'm fine.
12:
No need to keep secrets. We're
friends, aren't we? Perhaps there's
something I could help you with.
14:
That Righteous Swordswoman. She's
causing trouble for you, isn't she?
16:
Why the surprised look? I see
everything, you know.
17:
It's a replica of that sword made by
the Grand Creator... How interesting
that it fell into that little girl's hands.
19:
You'll work for me again, won't you?
My friend.
25:
Wowww! The Righteous
Swordswoman, for real! Give us your
autograph! Pleeease!
28:
U-um, okay. One person at a time,
though!
31:
Hey, hey! Say the thing! "I will right
the wrongs of this world!"
35:
Ahh... That might still be a little tough
for me!
47: Huh? You're not going to help?!
54:
Layna's gone missing in the
Kaleidoscope!
59:
She's not here, either... How did
Layna end up in this place—
62:
My daughter looked up to you. Even
though you were something so
improper as an adventurer.
64:
Every person has their place in life.
It's not wise to step outside of it.
86:
Stupid girl. You still don't realize
you've been tricked? Layna never
came to the Kaleidoscope to begin
with.
91:
You were after... the sword...
But it's no use! The holy sword only
responds to me—
97:
Sorry to disappoint you, but I have
an idea of how the sword works. But
you aren't mistaken in believing the
sword is a good fit for you.
98:
The sword's curse both consumes
and colors one's thoughts. Your
weakness made you the perfect
vessel.
104:
Now then, time to tie up loose ends.
Kill her, Redd.
106:
Kill her?! W-wait a minute. We never
talked about killing any—
108:
What's wrong, Redd? This isn't like
you. Don't overthink this.
109:
Have you forgotten? The guilt and
responsibility all fall to me. It's not
your role to worry about such things.
111:
So. All you have to do is shut up and
do what I say.
118: That's wrong! Redd, this isn't true!
122:
There's always a choice! For
everyone!
135:
After all I've done for you... You were
nothing but a third-rate adventurer
when we first met. What a shame.
137:
Well, no matter. You'll make a good
sacrifice for the sword. You hear me,
friend?
152:
The hell are you doing?! You know
you can do this!
169:
I will eliminate the wrongs of this
world!
187:
I guess that's one less thing we need
to worry about.
190:
Still, not a trace of that Star Augur's
deeds remains... It's certainly
impressive.
193:
I've lost everything. My standing, my
wealth, my honor...
195: But, still. I feel relieved... Thank you.
198: ...Of course. I'll take care of Layna.
202:
Okay, then. Let's head back and
grab a drink.
205:
Splendid work, Rinoa! There's no
doubt about it, you truly are the
Righteous Swordswoman!
207:
Please, tell us anything you'd like!
Strike a pose and say your
catchphrase!
214: Come on. We know you can do this.
222:
I am the Righteous Swordswoman,
and I will right all the wrong worlds!
233:
Wahhh! It's still too embarrassing to
pull it off on my own!
